Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe and US Vice President Mike Pence held a joint press conference in Tokyo, where they discussed various issues including North Korea, China, and trade. They emphasized the strong bond between Japan and the US and their commitment to work together to achieve the complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. They also discussed the importance of a free and open Indo-Pacific, and the need for fair and reciprocal trade between the two countries. Abe expressed his appreciation for the US' support and investments in Japan's self-defense, and Pence praised Japan's efforts in maintaining peace and security in the region. Overall, both leaders expressed optimism about the future of the US-Japan alliance and their continued cooperation in various areas.